{ SHELLOW CROSS FARM}is a mushroom farm. The owners used to have turkeys on the farm which were sold at christmas, now they have just mushrooms and some crops.
The house is about 285 years old It is a reasonably big farm. They have 380 acres of land in which to grow their crops.
They have 8 sheds for mushroom growing. The mushrooms grow on beds with peat in them. The beds are stacked up on top of each other. 4 or 5 beds are put on top each other. When the mushrooms are cut all the boxes with them in are taken to shops or houses which have ordered them. There are 4 sorts of mushrooms{OPENS, CUPS, {FLATS and BUTTONS.}
